ref%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-has-slashed-more-manager-roles-in-its-efficiency-drive-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estripping%20back%20management%20layers%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20this%20time%20by%20flattening%20teams%20in%20its%20core%20US%20ad%20sales%20unit%2C%20Business%20Insider%20has%20learned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20employees%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-sales-team-focus-mid-size-advertisers-performance-max-ai-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle%20Customer%20Solutions%3C%2Fa%3E%20(GCS)%20division%20were%20informed%20last%20month%20that%20several%20changes%20to%20the%20leadership%20structure%20would%20take%20effect%20in%20January%2C%20in%20a%20memo%20sent%20by%20its%20vice%20president%2C%20John%20Nicoletti.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20latest%20restructuring%20shows%20how%20even%20the%20most%20profitable%20corners%20of%20Big%20Tech%20are%20moving%20to%20run%20leaner%20and%20faster.%20Google's%20ad%20business%2C%20which%20still%20accounts%20for%20the%20bulk%20of%20its%20revenue%2C%20is%20flattening%20management%20layers%20to%20speed%20up%20decisions%20and%20reduce%20bureaucracy%20as%20growth%20slows%20and%20competition%20from%20AI-driven%20rivals%20intensifies.%20In%20an%20all-hands%20meeting%20in%20August%2C%20Google%20leaders%20told%20staff%20that%20the%20company%20had%20reduced%20the%20number%20of%20managers%20overseeing%20small%20teams%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-has-slashed-more-manager-roles-in-its-efficiency-drive-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E35%25%20over%20the%20previous%20year%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20changes%20inside%20GCS%2C%20which%20serves%20midsize%20advertisers%2C%20reflect%20a%20wider%20trend%20across%20the%20tech%20industry%3A%20the%20end%20of%20cushy%20managerial%20hierarchies%20in%20a%20cost-conscious%20era.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20change%20will%20be%20to%20remove%20the%20layer%20of%20%26quot%3BManagers%20of%20Managers%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20MoMs%2C%20across%20several%20teams%2C%20Nicoletti%20said%20in%20the%20memo%2C%20which%20was%20reviewed%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20No%20layoffs%20were%20mentioned%20in%20the%20email%2C%20which%20said%20the%20affected%20employees%20would%20move%20into%20other%20roles.%20The%20exact%20number%20of%20manager%20roles%20being%20removed%20could%20not%20be%20learned%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnlocking%20our%20next%20stage%20of%20growth%20means%20building%20our%20team%20strategy%20and%20structure%20for%20the%20long%20term%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicoletti%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Google%20spokesperson%20confirmed%20the%20changes%20to%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20teams%20have%20continued%20to%20make%20changes%20to%20operate%20more%20efficiently%2C%20remove%20layers%2C%20and%20better%20serve%20our%20customers%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20spokesperson%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENicoletti%20said%20the%20changes%20in%20ad%20sales%20in%20January%20would%20%26quot%3BEmpower%20our%20teams%2C%20with%20a%20focus%20on%20agility%20to%20accelerate%20decision-making%2C%20and%20keeping%20leadership%20close%20to%20the%20work%20by%20simplifying%20our%20organizational%20structure.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAd%20sales%20is%20a%20critical%20part%20of%20Google's%20business%2C%20and%20GCS%20%E2%80%94%20which%20focuses%20on%20midsize%20clients%20%E2%80%94%20is%20the%20central%20engine.%20In%20the%20September%20memo%20to%20staff%2C%20Nicoletti%20described%20GCS%20as%20%26quot%3Bmanaging%20a%20portfolio%20the%20size%20of%20a%20Fortune%20100%20company.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20the%20upcoming%20January%20changes%20for%20GCS%2C%20Nicoletti%20said%20all%20managers%20across%20select%20teams%20would%20become%20%26quot%3BHeads%20of%20business%26quot%3B%20and%20report%20directly%20to%20directors%20with%20no%20management%20layer%20in%20between.%20This%20would%20include%20removing%20a%20layer%20within%20its%20mid-market%20sales%20group%20%E2%80%94%20a%20role%20known%20as%20account%20strategy%20management%20%E2%80%94%20that%20previously%20stood%20between%20account%20executives%20and%20managers%2C%20and%20the%20heads%20of%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20told%20staff%20that%20Google%20would%20reopen%20account%20executive%20roles%20%26quot%3Bto%20continue%20investing%20in%20capacity%20for%20deep%20customer%20partnerships.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20of%20the%20reasons%20that%20we've%20been%20so%20successful%20is%20that%20we're%20outstanding%20at%20driving%20momentum%20through%20continuous%20change%2C%26quot%3B%20Nicoletti%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThis%20will%20be%20no%20different.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGoogle%20is%20not%20alone%20in%20reducing%20management%20layers.%20In%20recent%20years%2C%20tech%20giants%20such%20as%20Intel%2C%20Amazon%2C%20and%20Microsoft%20have%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-amazon-google-embrace-flatter-structure-fewer-managers-boost-efficiency-2025-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eflattened%20their%20management%20structures%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20an%20effort%20to%20become%20more%20efficient.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGCS%20was%20the%20only%20division%20mentioned%20in%20Nicoletti's%20memo%2C%20but%20it's%20not%20the%20only%20team%20in%20ad%20sales.%20It%20also%20has%20teams%20working%20on%20Large%20Customer%20Sales%20(LCS)%2C%20which%20focus%20on%20the%20biggest%20and%20most%20complex%20customers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%202024%2C%20Google's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-is-laying-off-hundreds-of-employees-in-its-advertising-team-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Echief%20business%20officer%2C%20Philipp%20Schindler%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20told%20staff%20that%20GCS%20would%20become%20the%20%26quot%3Bcore%20channel%20for%20scaling%20growth%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20company%20pared%20back%20teams%20on%20LCS.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20something%20to%20share%3F%20Contact%20this%20reporter%20via%20e