F3c8d%2Flive%2Fbe9d1a50-af65-11f0-b932-d752a474c44a.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcd9k2w8ell0o%230%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20is%20the%20eighth%20US%20strike%20on%20alleged%20drug%20trafficking%20vessels%20near%20Latin%20America%2C%20the%20first%20on%20the%20Pacific%20side.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A665%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcd9k2w8ell0o%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcd9k2w8ell0o.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2Fcd9k2w8ell0o.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Reddit%20drags%20Perplexity%20in%20a%20new%20lawsuit%2C%20accusing%20it%20of%20building%20up%20a%20%2420%20billion%20company%20off%20stolen%20data%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Reddit%20artificial%20intelligence%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68f90c88599d46a4ccc0a3e1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223337%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EReddit%20is%20suing%20Perplexity%20and%20other%20AI%20firms%2C%20accusing%20them%20of%20bypassing%20digital%20guardrails%20to%20steal%20valuable%20data.%3Cp%3EIllustration%20by%20Avishek%20Das%2FSOPA%20Images%2FLightRocket%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EReddit%20has%20accused%20Perplexity%20and%20other%20data%20scrapers%20of%20stealing%20valuable%20data.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20new%20lawsuit%20claims%20the%20firms%20bypassed%20Reddit's%20digital%20guardrails%20using%20Google.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EReddit%20said%20the%20companies%20have%20been%20selling%20its%20proprietary%20data%20to%20train%20AI%20models.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20against%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-data-trap-catches-perplexity-impersonating-google-cloudflare-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EPerplexity%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20along%20with%20several%20other%20data%20mining%20companies%2C%20accusing%20them%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fopenai-anthropic-ai-ignore-rule-scraping-web-contect-robotstxt%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Estealing%20the%20social%20media%20platform's%3C%2Fa%3E%20valuable%20data.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit's%20lawsuit%2C%20filed%20on%20Wednesday%20in%20Manhattan%20federal%20court%2C%20said%20Perplexity%20and%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20three%20other%20firms%20it%20sued%20%E2%80%94%20Oxylabs%20UAB%2C%20AWM%20Proxy%2C%20and%20SerpApi%20%E2%80%94%20illegally%20circumvented%20Reddit's%20digital%20guardrails%20by%20scraping%20its%20content%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcloudflare-google-ai-overviews-license-bots-scraping-content-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EGoogle's%20search%20engine%3C%2Fa%3E%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20Defendants%20are%20similar%20to%20would-be%20bank%20robbers%2C%20who%2C%20knowing%20they%20cannot%20get%20into%20the%20bank%20vault%2C%20break%20into%20the%20armored%20truck%20carrying%20the%20cash%20instead%2C%26quot%3B%20Reddit's%20lawsuit%20alleges.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%20said%20it%20sent%20a%20cease-and-desist%20letter%20to%20Perplexity%20in%20May%202024%20demanding%20it%20stop%20scraping%20Reddit%20data%20unless%20it%20made%20a%20deal%20with%20the%20social%20media%20company%2C%20as%20Google%20and%20OpenAI%20had%20done.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerplexity%20said%20it%20%26quot%3Bwas%20not%20using%20Reddit%20content%20to%20train%20any%20AI%20models%20and%20that%20it%20would%20respect%20Reddit's%20robots.txt%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20lawsuit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Perplexity's%20citations%20to%20Reddit%20increased%20%26quot%3Bforty-fold%20after%20Reddit%20told%20it%20to%20stop%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRather%20than%20respect%20Reddit%20and%20its%20users'%20rights%2C%20what%20Perplexity%20has%20done%20in%20response%20is%20simply%20come%20up%20with%20increasingly%20devious%20schemes%20to%20circumvent%20Reddit's%20security%20systems%20and%20policies%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20lawsuit%2C%20Perplexity%20appears%20to%20have%20used%20at%20least%20one%20of%20the%20data%20scrapers%20to%20ingest%20the%20platform's%20data%20into%20its%20AI%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20other%20words%2C%20Perplexity's%20business%20model%20is%20effectively%20to%20take%20Reddit's%20content%20from%20Google%20search%20results%2C%20feed%20them%20into%20a%20third%20party's%20LLM%2C%20and%20call%20it%20a%20new%20product%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20lawsuit%20says.%20%26quot%3BWhile%20that%20business%20model%20has%20somehow%20translated%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fperplexity-valuation-jumps-to-20-billion-in-latest-fundraise-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ea%20%2420%20billion%20valuation%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20it%20has%20not%20resulted%20in%20a%20willingness%20to%20pay%20for%20what%20others%20(including%20Google)%20have.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerplexity%20spokesperson%20Jesse%20Dwyer%20said%20the%20company%20%26quot%3Bwill%20always%20fight%20vigorously%20for%20users'%20rights%20to%20freely%20and%20fairly%20access%20public%20knowledge.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20approach%20remains%20principled%20and%20responsible%20as%20we%20provide%20factual%20answers%20with%20accurate%20AI%2C%20and%20we%20will%20not%20tolerate%20threats%20against%20openness%20and%20the%20public%20interest%2C%26quot%3B%20Dwyer%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20SerpApi%20representative%20said%20the%20company%20disagrees%20with%20Reddit's%20allegations%20and%20plans%20to%20%26quot%3Bvigorously%26quot%3B%20defend%20itself%20in%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOxylabs%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20AWMProxy%2C%20identified%20in%20the%20lawsuit%20as%20a%20former%20Russian%20botnet%2C%20could%20not%20immediately%20be%20reached%20for%20comment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Reddit%20spokesperson%20confirmed%20to%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20company%20has%20spent%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20on%20anti-scraping%20systems%2C%20which%20the%20lawsuit%20says%20these%20companies%20circumvented.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20lawsuit%20said%20Reddit%20caught%20Perplexity%20bypassing%20its%20guardrails%20by%20setting%20up%20a%20test%20post%20that%20acted%20as%20a%20digital%20%26quot%3Bmarked%20bill.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20test%20post%20could%20only%20be%20viewed%20by%20Google's%20search%20engine%2C%20the%20lawsuit%20said%2C%20so%20Perplexity%20and%20other%20AI%20companies%20should%20not%20have%20been%20able%20to%20use%20it%20for%20their%20models.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20contents%20of%20the%20post%20soon%20appeared%20in%20Perplexity%2C%20indicating%20that%20it%20or%20another%20data%20scraper%20it%20worked%20with%20had%20taken%20the%20content%20without%20permission.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWithin%20hours%2C%20queries%20to%20Perplexity's%20'answer%20engine'%20produced%20the%20contents%20of%20that%20test%20post%2C%26quot%3B%20Reddit's%20lawsuit%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit's%20lawsuit%20quotes%20a%20social%20media%20post%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmatthew-prince-search-engines-ai-cloudflare-google-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ECloudflare's%20CEO%3C%2Fa%3E%20comparing%20Perplexity%20to%20%26quot%3BNorth%20Korean%20hackers%26quot%3B%20for%20appearing%20to%20try%20to%20hide%20its%20web-crawling%20activity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSome%20supposedly%20'reputable'%20AI%20companies%20act%20more%20like%20North%20Korean%20hackers%2C%26quot%3B%20Matthew%20Prince%20wrote%20on%20X%20in%20August.%20%26quot%3BTime%20to%20name%2C%20shame%2C%20and%20hard%20block%20them.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20to%20Business%20Insider%2C%20Reddit's%20chief%20legal%20officer%20Ben%20Lee%20said%20Oxylabs%20UAB%2C%20AWM%20Proxy%2C%20and%20SerpApi%20were%20%26quot%3Btextbook%20examples%26quot%3B%20of%20illegal%20scrapers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BScrapers%20bypass%20technological%20protections%20to%20steal%20data%2C%20then%20sell%20it%20to%20clients%20hungry%20for%20training%20material%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BReddit%20is%20a%20prime%20target%20because%20it's%20one%20of%20the%20largest%20and%20most%20dynamic%20collections%20of%20human%20conversation%20ever%20created.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReddit%20launched%20in%202005%20as%20an%20online%20discussion%20forum%2C%20but%20is%20now%20trying%20to%20add%20value%20through%20a%20new%20strategy%3A%20search%20traffic.%20The%20decision%20has%20put%20Reddit%20in%20competition%20with%20companies%20like%20Perplexity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BReddit%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20platforms%20positioned%20to%20become%20a%20true%20search%20destination.%20We%20offer%20something%20special%3A%20a%20breadth%20of%20conversations%20and%20knowledge%20you%20can't%20find%20anywhere%20else%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20company%20said%20in%20its%20Q2%20report%20in%20July.%20%26quot%3BEvery%20week%2C%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20people%20come%20to%20Reddit%20looking%20for%20advice%2C%20and%20we're%20turning%20more%20of%20that%20intent%20into%20active%20users%20of%20Reddit's%20native%20search.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnline%20search%20traffic%20has%20become%20a%20profitable%20industry%20led%20by%20companies%20like%20Google%2C%20which%20announced%20an%20expanded%20partnership%20with%20Reddit%20in%20March%202024%20to%20train%20its%20AI%20models%20on%20the%20platform's%20content.%20On%20its%20end%2C%20Reddit%20gained%20access%20to%20Google's%20Vertex%20AI%2C%20allowing%20the%20platform%20to%20add%20enhanced%20search%20and%20other%20features.%20One%20month%20later%2C%20Reddit%20went%20public%20with%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freddit-execs-shar